---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, GAME } from '../consts';

const faq = [
  { q: 'Can you customize your character in Moonlight Peaks?', a: 'Yes. There is a full character creator — already playable in the free demo — where you set your vampire\u2019s skin tone, eyes, hairstyle, makeup and outfits. The options are designed to be inclusive of any style, with a supernatural twist.' },
  { q: 'Is the Moonlight Peaks character creator gender-neutral?', a: 'Yes. The character models are intentionally gender-neutral, and dating is not gender-locked, so you can build the vampire you want and romance anyone regardless of how you present.' },
  { q: 'Can you change your appearance after creating your character?', a: 'Yes, via two separate confirmed methods: a mirror in your house lets you freely change clothing (and some other customization) any time for free, while the Alter Ego Elixir — a one-time, 1,300-gold potion from Sabrina — changes hairstyle, hair color, skin tone, eye color, eyebrows, and makeup, but not clothing. Your character\u2019s name is the one thing that can\u2019t be changed later.' },
  { q: 'How do you change clothes in Moonlight Peaks?', a: 'Confirmed: use the mirror inside your house to change clothing (Outfit Sets, Tops, Bottoms, Shoes) and accessories (Arms, Face) any time, for free. This is separate from the Alter Ego Elixir, which does not affect clothing. New clothing is bought from Aras at Third Eye Threads; anything you wore during character creation is already permanently unlocked in your wardrobe.' },
];

const jsonLd = [
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: faq.map((f) => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: f.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a } })) },
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Character creator', item: new URL('/character-creator', SITE.url).href },
  ] },
];
---
<Base
  title="Moonlight Peaks Character Creator — Customization Options"
  description="How character creation works in Moonlight Peaks: the demo's vampire creator — skin tones, eyes, hairstyles, makeup, and outfits, gender-neutral and inclusive."
  path="/character-creator"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Character creator' }]}
  showExport
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Entry · Character creator</p>
      <h1>Moonlight Peaks <em>character creator</em></h1>
      <p class="intro">
        Before you tend a single moonlit crop, you design your vampire. Here's what {GAME.title}'s
        character creator lets you do — based on the official details and the free demo, which already
        includes it. Updated {SITE.updated}.
      </p>

      <h2>Try it now in the free demo</h2>
      <p>
        The character creator is one of the headline features of the free demo on Steam and the
        Nintendo eShop, so you can build your vampire and experiment with looks — see our
        <a href="/demo">demo guide</a> for what else is included.
      </p>

      <h2>What you can customize</h2>
      <p>
        You shape your vampire's appearance across skin tones, eyes (confirmed: each eye can be set
        to a different colour), hairstyle and colour, facial details, and outfit — with a wide
        wardrobe from the start and more to buy as you progress. The studio describes the options as
        inclusive of any style, all with a supernatural flair — whether you want to look casual,
        whimsical, or, fittingly, drop-dead gorgeous.
      </p>

      <h2>Clothing and outfits, confirmed details</h2>
      <p>
        Confirmed: clothing is organized into Outfit Sets, Tops, Bottoms, and Shoes, plus a separate
        Accessories category (Arms, Face). Whatever you wear during character creation is
        <strong>permanently unlocked in your wardrobe</strong> — you never have to re-buy your
        starting outfit later. New clothing after that is bought from <a href="/characters/aras">Aras</a>
        at Third Eye Threads. Multi-source confirmed: hairstyles alone run to <strong>35 cuts</strong>,
        plus another <strong>30 dedicated beard-and-moustache options</strong>, with hair, brow, and
        facial-hair colour all chosen separately. There are also two full portrait styles to choose
        between — the default painterly look and an alternative anime-style set — which changes how
        every character (including you) is drawn in dialogue and menus.
      </p>

      <h2>Changing your look later: mirror vs. potion</h2>
      <p>
        Confirmed: these are two separate systems. A <strong>mirror inside your house</strong> lets
        you freely change clothing and some other customization at any time, at no cost. Separately,
        the <strong>Alter Ego Elixir</strong> — a one-time, 1,300-gold potion sold by Sabrina at Webb
        of Wonders — changes hairstyle, hair colour, skin tone, eye colour, eyebrows, and makeup, but
        explicitly does <strong>not</strong> affect clothing or accessories. Your character's name is
        the one choice that can't be changed later by either method.
      </p>

      <h2>Naming three things</h2>
      <p>
        Confirmed at launch: character creation has you name three things — yourself, your farm,
        and your three-eyed Hellkitten companion, who joins you as you leave home. None of this
        affects gameplay or your romance options; it's purely for your own fun.
      </p>

      <h2>Gender-neutral by design</h2>
      <p>
        Character models are intentionally gender-neutral, and the dating system isn't gender-locked.
        In other words, you build the vampire you want and can <a href="/romance">romance</a> any
        eligible resident regardless of how you present.
      </p>

      <h2>Not locked in — the Alter Ego Elixir</h2>
      <p>
        If you change your mind later, you won't be stuck with your starting look: the
        <strong>Alter Ego Elixir</strong>, one of the potions you can brew, changes your appearance.
        See <a href="/magic">magic & potions</a> for how brewing works.
      </p>

      <h2>Still being verified</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The full list of <strong>options</strong> — hairstyles, faces, skin tones and outfit pieces.</li>
        <li>Whether there are <strong>presets</strong> and how much you can fine-tune.</li>
        <li>Any cosmetics or styles you <strong>unlock</strong> over the course of the full game.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        {faq.map((f) => (
          <details>
            <summary>{f.q}</summary>
            <p>{f.a}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="callout wip">
        Pre-launch entry — full option lists land at launch. Related:
        <a href="/shapeshifting">shapeshifting</a>, <a href="/characters">characters</a>,
        <a href="/demo">the demo</a>.
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
